Package xrf_test
-----------------------------------------------
Description: This package allows for testing the RELbot in a raw state, sending FSM commands and wheel speeds.

Building instructions: Place folder in src. Build normally via colcon build.

*****Node: tester*****
Input:
/XenoState
        Type: std_msgs/msg/Int32
        FSM state

Output:
/input/left_motor/setpoint_vel
        Type: example_interfaces/msg/Float64
        Left wheel speed, decimal ratio of maximum.
        
/input/right_motor/setpoint_vel
	Type: example_interfaces/msg/Float64
        Right wheel speed, decimal ratio of maximum.

/XenoCmd
	Type:std_msgs/msg/Int32
	FSM command

Run:
	ros2 launch xrf_test xrf_test.launch.py
	# Change parameters during runtime 
	ros2 param set /tester setpoints_array "[2.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0]"

Parameters:
	reliability: [string] reliability policy used by QoS
	durability: [string] durability policy used by QoS
	history: [string] history policy used by QoS
	depth: [int] Amount of messages to keep for history policy
	FSMcomm: [int] command for FSM
	rightSpeed: [double] Right wheel speed, decimal ratio of maximum.
	leftSpeed: [double] Left wheel speed, decimal ratio of maximum.
	setpoints_array: [double[]] Sequence for testing, format: [duration, FSM, rightSpeed, leftSpeed, ...]
	
Core components: 
	timer_callback(): Run the appropriate sequence periodically
	sequence(): Parse sequence and run publish function
	publish_command(): Publish FSM command and wheel speeds
	loop_callback(): Get and print FSM state
	
